definitions.definition: Originally ( music ) , a performing engagement by a musician or musical group ; ( by extension , film , television , theater ) a job or role for a performer .
examples: I caught one of the Rolling Stones ’ first gigs in Richmond.
Hey, when are we gonna get that hotel gig again?

definitions.definition: ( by extension ) Any job, especially one that is freelance or temporary , or done on an on-demand basis .
examples: I had this gig as a file clerk but it wasn’t my style so I left.
That guy’s got a great gig over at the bike shop. He hardly works all day.

definitions.definition: ( US , military ) A demerit received for some infraction of a military deportment or dress code .
examples: I received gigs for having buttons of my uniform undone.

main_definition: Originally ( music ) , a performing engagement by a musician or musical group ; ( by extension , film , television , theater ) a job or role for a performer .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) Any job, especially one that is freelance or temporary , or done on an on-demand basis .
( US , military ) A demerit received for some infraction of a military deportment or dress code .

definitions.definition: ( informal , computing ) Clipping of gigabyte ( “ one billion (1,000,000,000) bytes ” ) .
examples: This picture is almost a gig ; don’t you want to resize it?
My new computer has over 500 gigs of hard drive space.

definitions.definition: ( slang , chiefly sciences ) Any unit of measurement having the SI prefix giga- .

main_definition: ( informal , computing ) Clipping of gigabyte ( “ one billion (1,000,000,000) bytes ” ) .
secondary_definitions: ( slang , chiefly sciences ) Any unit of measurement having the SI prefix giga- .

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) A top which is made to spin by tying a piece of string around it and then throwing it so that the string unwinds rapidly ; a whipping -top.
( chiefly British , school slang ( Eton College ) , archaic or dialectal ) A person with an odd appearance ; also, a foolish person.

subdefinitions.definition: ( slang , archaic or British , dialectal ) Fun ; frolics .
( obsolete ) A fanciful impulse ; a whim ; also, a joke .

( nautical ) A small , narrow , open boat carried in a larger ship , and used for transportation between the ship and the shore , another vessel , etc. ( Southern England , by extension ) A similar rowing boat or sailboat , especially one used for racing ; specifically, a six - oared sea rowing boat commonly found in Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly .
( road transport , historical ) A two - wheeled carriage drawn by a single horse .

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) A frivolous , playful , or wanton young woman ; a giglet or giglot .

definitions.definition: Synonym of fishgig or fizgig ( “ a spear with a barb on the end of it, used for catching fish , frogs , or other small animals ” ) .
